# Ingestion and Parsing

- Keep the implementation fully Rust-native and storage-free (no DuckDB/cache layers).
- Resolve the ingestion root from `SIMPLEMMR_HOME` when set; otherwise use the real home directory.
- Parse JSONL defensively: skip malformed lines and continue ingesting valid records.
- Preserve deterministic ordering metadata (`source_file`, `line_index`) for stable sorting.
- Maintain parallel ingest using `rayon` across all source loaders (Codex, Claude, Cursor, Grok, and Pi).

## Example

```rust
// ✅ GOOD: defensive parsing
let value: Value = match serde_json::from_str(line) {
    Ok(value) => value,
    Err(_) => continue,
};

// ❌ BAD: aborts on first malformed line
let value: Value = serde_json::from_str(line)?;
```
